quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  42,10,"ňĻSay to the believers, O Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWhatever you may differ about, its judgment rests with God. That is God‚ÄĒmy Lord. In Him I put my trust, and to Him I ňĻalwaysňļ turn.‚ÄĚ"
  42,11,"ňĻHe isňļ the Originator of the heavens and the earth. He has made for you spouses from among yourselves, and ňĻmadeňļ mates for cattle ňĻas wellňļ‚ÄĒmultiplying you ňĻbothňļ. There is nothing like Him, for He ňĻaloneňļ is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  42,12,"To Him belong the keys ňĻof the treasuriesňļ of the heavens and the earth. He gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills. Indeed, He has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  42,13,"He has ordained for you ňĻbelieversňļ the Way which He decreed for Noah, and what We have revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ and what We decreed for Abraham, Moses, and Jesus,¬†ňĻcommanding:ňļ ‚ÄúUphold the faith, and make no divisions in it.‚ÄĚ What you call the polytheists to is unbearable for them. God chooses for Himself whoever He wills, and guides to Himself whoever turns ňĻto Himňļ"
  42,14,"They did not split ňĻinto sectsňļ out of mutual envy until knowledge came to them.¬†Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord for an appointed term,¬†the matter would have certainly been settled between them ňĻat onceňļ. And surely those who were made to inherit the Scripture¬†after them are truly in alarming doubt about this ňĻQuranňļ"
  42,15,"Because of that, you ňĻO Prophetňļ will invite ňĻallňļ. Be steadfast as you are commanded, and do not follow their desires. And say, ‚ÄúI believe in every Scripture God has revealed. And I am commanded to judge fairly among you. God is our Lord and your Lord. We will be accountable for our deeds and you for yours. There is no ňĻneed forňļ contention between us. God will gather us together ňĻfor judgmentňļ. And to Him is the final return.‚ÄĚ"
  42,16,"As for those who dispute about God after He is ňĻalreadyňļ acknowledged ňĻby manyňļ, their argument is futile in the sight of their Lord. Upon them is wrath, and they will suffer a severe punishment"
  42,17,"It is God Who has revealed the Book with the truth and the balance ňĻof justiceňļ. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near"
  42,18,"Those who disbelieve in it ňĻask toňļ hasten it ňĻmockinglyňļ. But the believers are fearful of it, knowing that it is the truth. Surely those who dispute about the Hour have gone far astray"
  42,19,"God is Ever Kind to His servants. He provides ňĻabundantlyňļ to whoever He wills. And He is the All-Powerful, Almighty"